'''Nkandla''' ke toropo ya uThungulu setereke sa KwaZulu-Natal, [[Afrika Borwa]]. Ke setulo sa [[Mmasepala wa Selegae wa Nkandla]], le setereke seo go sona [[Nkandla (homestead)|mafelo a bodulo]] wa peleng [[Mopresidente wa Afrika Borwa]], [[Jacob Zuma]], e lego e lego gona. Lefelo la bodulo le dikhilomithara tše 40 ka borwa bja toropo ya Nkandla, ka kua ga Sethokgwa sa Nkandla le tseleng ya go ya [[Kranskop]].

Selete sa Nkandla se akaretša badudi ba go nyakile go ba 115,000, ba phatlaletše ka sewelo godimo ga lefelo le legolo. Nkandla kudu ke lefelo la magaeng gomme le mafelong a mahlano a godimo ao a diilago kudu profenseng ya KwaZulu-Natal. Bodiidi bo atile, ka 44% ya tlhokego ya mešomo. Bontši bja baagi ke Bazulu.<ref>http://citizen.co.za/147907/zumas-guilded-battlements-besieged/|title=Zuma’s guilded battlements besieged|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140322224913/http://citizen.co.za/147907/zumas-guilded-battlements-besieged/|archive-date=22 March 2014|url-status=unfit}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://you.co.za/news/six-reasons-why-public-protector-thuli-madonselas-nkandla-report-is-important/|title = YOU}}</ref>

Taodiša ya 2004, ''[[Ditšhiwana tša Nkandla]]'', tša BBC le Truevision, di ile tša anega mathata le bodiidi bja ditšhiwana ka Nkandla.

Zuma o ile a kopanywa le [[Nelson Mandela]] go bula Sekolo se Segolo sa Mnyakanya ka 2004.<ref>{{cite news | title = South Africa: Zuma, Mandela to open school | newspaper = South African Government News Agency| last =  Mokgola | first = Thabo |date = 3 March 2004 | url = http://allafrica.com/stories/200403030546.html | accessdate = 11 March 2012}}</ref>
